
Description

integers.opal is a network that can interpret all integers in digits from 0 to 100,000 0 to 100,000 and 
integers expressed alpha-numerically from zero to ninety-nine hundred and ninety-nine. The output format is XML.


Integration Notes


Known Issues

The network does not support negative integers. 
The network does not support thousands if written in letters.
